<li id="cite_note-291"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-291">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation">"Guinness World Records earmarks licensing growth", <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.licensing.biz/news/6235/Guinness-World-Records-earmarks-licensing-growth"><i>Licensing</i></a>, 26 October 2010, <q>The Guinness Book of World Records has been published in 30 languages in more than 100 countries and has sold in excess of 115 million copies, becoming the biggest selling copyright book of all time.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Guinness+World+Records+earmarks+licensing+growth&amp;rft.btitle=Licensing&amp;rft.date=2010-10-26&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.licensing.biz%2Fnews%2F6235%2FGuinness-World-Records-earmarks-licensing-growth&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AList+of+best-selling+books" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>
